16 SECTION 2.
17 Said Act is further amended by revising subsections (b) and (e) of Section 9 as follows:
18 "(b) The board shall comply fully with the provisions of Chapter 14 of Title 50 of the
19 O.C.G.A., relating to open meetings, and Article 4 of Chapter 18 of Title 50 of the
20 O.C.G.A., relating to open records. The board shall ensure that the public has adequate
21 access to its meetings."
22 "(e) The elections director shall be responsible for training or causing to be trained all
23 employees of the board and all poll workers in election laws and procedures."
24 SECTION 3.
25 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 10 as follows:
26 "SECTION 10.
27 The elections director shall be responsible for the selection, appointment, and training of
28 all poll workers in elections, and such workers shall be appointed, insofar as practicable,
29 from lists provided to the board by the county executive committee of each political party."
30 SECTION 4.
31 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 12 as follows:
32 "SECTION 12.
33 (a) There shall be an administrative director, to be known as the elections director, to
34 administer and supervise the conduct of elections, primaries, and registration of electors
35 for the county who shall serve at the pleasure of the board. The board shall act to appoint
36 such administrative director or elections director within 60 days of the effective date of this
37 section, or of the date of any vacancy in such position. Such elections director shall be a
