38 legal resident of and registered to vote in Spalding County and shall remain a legal resident
39 of and a registered elector of Spalding County while serving as elections director.
40 (b) The elections director shall be a full-time employee and shall not have any other
41 employment while in such position. The elections director shall be an employee of
42 Spalding County and shall be entitled to all benefits available to other employees.
43 (c) Compensation for the elections director shall be set by the board consistent with the
44 budget of the board approved by the governing authority of Spalding County. Such
45 compensation shall be paid wholly from county funds.
46 (d) The elections director shall be authorized to employ such full-time and part-time
47 employees as the elections director shall deem necessary, provided that the same is
48 consistent with the budget of the board approved by the governing authority of Spalding
49 County. All such employees shall be legal residents of and registered to vote in Spalding
50 County and shall remain legal residents of and registered electors of Spalding County while
51 employed by the board.
52 (e) No person who holds an elective public office shall be eligible to serve as elections
53 director or as an employee of the elections office during the term of his or her elective
54 office, and the position of elections director or any employee of the elections office shall
55 be deemed vacant upon such person qualifying as a candidate in any primary or election
56 for public office. No person shall be eligible to serve as elections director or employee of
57 the elections office while holding any public office to which he or she was appointed or
58 while he or she is a salaried employee of the governing authority of Spalding County or of
59 any municipality within the county or of any board of education or commission, board, or
60 authority appointed by the governing authority of the county or any municipality within the
61 county."
62 SECTION 5.
63 Said Act is further amended by revising subsection (b) of Section 14 as follows:
